description:
## Design Reference
@docs/design/macos-desktop-redesign.md#data-model-changes

## Context
The menu bar quick capture feature needs to track recently used directories and the last used directory. These settings enable the menu bar to default to a sensible directory without user input.

## Requirements
- [ ] Add lastUsedDirectory: String? property with UserDefaults persistence
- [ ] Add recentDirectories: [String] property with UserDefaults persistence
- [ ] Implement trackDirectoryUsage(_ directory: String) method
- [ ] Initialize properties from UserDefaults in init()
- [ ] Limit recentDirectories to 10 entries
- [ ] Remove duplicates when tracking (most recent moves to front)

## Technical Approach
- Files to modify: ios/VoiceCode/AppSettings.swift
- Dependencies: None (can be done early)

Implementation:
```swift
@Published var lastUsedDirectory: String? {
    didSet { UserDefaults.standard.set(lastUsedDirectory, forKey: "lastUsedDirectory") }
}

@Published var recentDirectories: [String] {
    didSet { UserDefaults.standard.set(recentDirectories, forKey: "recentDirectories") }
}

func trackDirectoryUsage(_ directory: String) {
    lastUsedDirectory = directory
    recentDirectories = ([directory] + recentDirectories.filter { $0 != directory }).prefix(10).map { $0 }
}
```

## Verification
- [ ] Unit test: trackDirectoryUsage deduplicates and limits to 10
- [ ] Unit test: lastUsedDirectory persists across app restarts
- [ ] Unit test: tracking "/a", "/b", "/a" results in ["/a", "/b"]

## Acceptance Criteria
Enables acceptance criteria #5 (menu bar quick capture)

## Parallelization
Can be worked alongside: MacOSRootView, SessionSidebarView
Required by: MenuBarExtra
